From: torch_npu-infra <torch_npu-infra@example.com>
Date: Fri, 7 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix compatibility with PyTorch main branch CachingHostAllocator

PyTorch main branch changed the CachingHostAllocatorImpl interface:
- BlockPool is now a type alias to HostBlockPool<S_, E_, B_>
- process_events() signature changed
- HostBlockPool members renamed (blocks -> blocks_)

This patch:
1. Renames torch_npu's BlockPool to NPUBlockPool to avoid name conflict
2. Removes override keyword from process_events()
3. Updates all references to use NPUBlockPool

diff --git a/torch_npu/csrc/core/npu/CachingHostAllocator.cpp b/torch_npu/csrc/core/npu/CachingHostAllocator.cpp
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
